{"author":{"id":"cad0afbc936f740fb6048ec11d7d44bbdf0daf9970a4dbb5cf01894d5825487d"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1704860784,"nonce":"htJm5CLZJ+SxhwSAoQ/bQQ7ALiE=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s57mAjB","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/5703","origin":"github"},"title":"Names of log files from Trimmomatic don't correctly reflect inputs","message":"Issue with Trimmomatic output log files: \n\nSummary: can outputs be renamed differently? \n\nRunning on Galaxy Australia, Trimmomatic version 0.36.6\n\nInputs: Paired-end reads: 2 collections (one of R1 files, one of R2 files)\n\nOutput required: Trimmed reads, and a collection of log files (not trimlog files). \n\nThis log output is created properly, with one log file for every pair of input files, in a collection called something like \"Trimmomatic on collection 5 and collection 10 (log file)\". However, each log file is labelled with the same name as the R1 input file only, such as `sample123_R1.fastqsanger` \n\nI think it would be better if it could be labelled without the R1 extension, such as `sample123.fastqsanger`\n\nThis would be clearer for the user, and also for downstream tools (such as plots in MultiQC, which are thus also labelled as being R1 files, when they are actually relating to both R1 and R2 files).","files":null}]}